<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7626235>
    dc:description "FIGURE 24. A–G, Teleophrys pococki Rathbun, 1924. A, Adult male (MZUSP 39583), cl 9.2 mm, cw 10 mm. B, Ovigerous female (MZUSP 40614), cl 7.8 mm, cw 8 mm. C, D, Ovigerous female (MZUSP 39687), cl 6.1 mm, cw 6.1 mm. E, Juvenile male (MZUSP 40699), cl 4.1 mm, cw 4 mm. Note the more granular carapace and spiniform anterolateral teeth. F, G, Juvenile" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7626235/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7626239>
    dc:description "FIGURE 25. A, Teleophrys pococki Rathbun, 1924, male juvenile (MZUSP 40599), cl 4 mm, cw 3.9 mm. Dorsal aspect of the carapace, outline. Note granular carapace and spiniform anterolateral teeth. B, C, Teleophrys ornatus Rathbun, 1901, juvenile male from the Fernando de Noronha Archipelago dredged between 13 m and 36 m (after Miers 1886: 89, pl. 10, figs 3a, b, as Mithrax sp.). Note legs cristate on upper and lower surfaces. Habitus, dorsal view (B), right cheliped, lateral view (C). Scale: A, 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7626239/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

